ActOther Than Statutory Authority
SubjectSmith's Landing First Nation ** SETTING APART ** LED-09-05
PrecisSetting apart of 1,012 hectares (2,500 acres) of land, including mines and minerals, for the use and benefit of the SMITH'S LANDING FIRST NATION as an addition to Thebathi Indian Reserve No. 196 and the reserve creation of Tsu Nedehe Túe Indian Reserve No. 196H and the reserve creation of ?ejere K’elni Kue (agera killnee qua) Indian Reserve No. 196I, in the Province of Alberta. The proposed addition to the First Nation’s main reserve, Thebathi Indian Reserve No. 196, is contiguous and is located within the Regional Municipality of Wood Buffalo, approximately 25 kilometres from the Town of Fort Smith, Northwest Territories. The two new reserve proposals are lands excised from Wood Buffalo National Park and are located approximately 55 kilometres south of the Town of Fort Smith.
